Pea Sooup Andersen's Original Pea Soup Recipe

2 cups green split peas
1 stalk celery, coarsely chopped
1 large carrot, peeled and coarsely chopped
1 small onion, peeled and chopped
1/4 teaspoon thyme
1 bay leaf, crumbled into very small pieces
Pinch cayenne pepper
1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt
Salt and pepper to taste

Sort the peas in a mesh strainer, removing any stones or impurities. Rinse
them clean.

Combine the peas, celery, carrot, onion, thyme, bay leaf and cayenne in a soup
pot and cover with 2 quarts (8 cups) of water.  Bring pot to a boil and cook
for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to a simmedr and cook another 20-25 minutes
untill peas are tender.

Strain through a fine sieve then reheat and serve!
